  "text": "Rats were fixed to a foam board in supine position under general anesthesia using chloral hydrate. Then, rat breast was scan was performed by a GE LightSpeed VCT (GE Healthcare, Little Chalfont, UK) 64-slice CT at 80 kV tube voltage, 150 mA tube current, and medium bowtie filter (0.625-mm half-value layer). CT images were scored according to the Radiologist's score (RADS) method as previously described [CITATION_1] .",
